And again.

65
00:03:43,623 --> 00:03:45,550
Seiji Amasawa.

66
00:03:45,644 --> 00:03:47,186
Seiji Amasawa.

67
00:03:47,270 --> 00:03:49,940
Seiji Amasawa. That's amazing.

68
00:03:50,252 --> 00:03:52,660
This guy checked out all
these books before I did.

69
00:03:59,742 --> 00:04:01,651
Seiji Amasawa, huh?

70
00:04:01,744 --> 00:04:03,404
What kind of person are you?

71
00:04:03,807 --> 00:04:05,680
I wonder if we're anything alike.

72
00:04:23,225 --> 00:04:24,340
Shizuku!

73
00:04:24,476 --> 00:04:26,142
For heaven sakes, get up!

74
00:04:26,148 --> 00:04:29,185
I'm leaving.

75
00:04:30,191 --> 00:04:32,350
Hey, did you sleep in your clothes again?

76
00:04:32,485 --> 00:04:34,276
You're so scatterbrained.

77
00:04:35,335 --> 00:04:36,794
Have a good day.

78
00:04:39,868 --> 00:04:42,538
Aah! Is it that late? I'm
supposed to meet Yuko.

79
00:04:44,939 --> 00:04:46,775
Ugh! My wallet!

80
00:04:47,876 --> 00:04:50,546
Did you get all the way
down the stairs again, Mom?

81
00:04:50,629 --> 00:04:51,827
Yes!

82
00:04:51,964 --> 00:04:54,087
Where is it?

83
00:04:54,644 --> 00:04:56,838
Is it by the telephone?

84
00:04:56,970 --> 00:04:59,778
- Found it!
- You always leave it there.

85
00:04:59,784 --> 00:05:01,343
I'm gonna be late!

86
00:05:01,349 --> 00:05:04,054
- Don't forget to lock up!
- Who's scatterbrained?

87
00:05:12,361 --> 00:05:14,934
Wow! I've never seen a blimp so close.

88
00:05:19,618 --> 00:05:21,446
Today's gonna be great.

89
00:05:47,286 --> 00:05:49,038
Hot day.

90
00:05:56,587 --> 00:05:58,046
Hi, Yappy.

91
00:05:58,052 --> 00:06:00,091
Can't you bark any louder than that?

92
00:06:22,417 --> 00:06:25,020
Shizuku! Shizuku! Hey, there.

93
00:06:25,026 --> 00:06:28,193
Hey, Michiko. Good luck
on your match today.

94
00:06:31,514 --> 00:06:33,589
Hi, Miss Kosaka. Can I come in?

95
00:06:33,749 --> 00:06:36,690
Oh, hi, Shizuku. What are you doing here?

96
00:06:37,078 --> 00:06:38,904
I need you to do me a favor.

97
00:06:39,036 --> 00:06:41,409
What? It's not something weird, is it?

98
00:06:41,415 --> 00:06:44,286
- Can you open the library, please?
- The library?

99
00:06:44,648 --> 00:06:46,848
Can't you wait until school starts?

100
00:06:47,369 --> 00:06:48,745
No. That's the point.

101
00:06:48,751 --> 00:06:51,751
I decided I was gonna read 20
books over summer vacation,

102
00:06:51,757 --> 00:06:53,911
and the city library doesn't
have the book I want.

103
00:06:54,024 --> 00:06:55,462
It'll just be a second.

104
00:06:55,468 --> 00:06:58,721
Twenty books? What about your
high school entrance exams?

105
00:06:58,727 --> 00:07:01,135
Can't you even pretend
to be studying for them?

106
00:07:01,762 --> 00:07:02,841
Uh, here it is.

107
00:07:02,937 --> 00:07:05,558
Hurry up and bring it here.

108
00:07:06,092 --> 00:07:09,313
Come on, give me your library card
and the checkout card from the book.

109
00:07:09,823 --> 00:07:11,448
Here you go.

110
00:07:12,667 --> 00:07:13,996
Hey, look at this.

111
00:07:14,002 --> 00:07:16,361
No one's ever checked this book out before.

112
00:07:16,731 --> 00:07:18,439
No one? What do you know.

113
00:07:18,526 --> 00:07:20,566
I finally beat Seiji Amasawa.

114
00:07:26,658 --> 00:07:30,072
Donated by... Amasawa?

115
00:07:30,646 --> 00:07:34,249
No way! Do you have any idea
who this Amasawa person is?

116
00:07:34,470 --> 00:07:37,091
Oh, now look, you made me make a mistake.

117
00:07:37,511 --> 00:07:39,511
Well, that guy's probably the book's donor.

118
00:07:39,517 --> 00:07:41,510
I don't know anyone from that long ago.

119
00:07:41,516 --> 00:07:44,007
- Ask one of the older teachers.
- Shizuku!

120
00:07:44,355 --> 00:07:47,191
I should have known you
were going to do this.

121
00:07:47,317 --> 00:07:49,549
You said to meet outside
the school, not inside.

122
00:07:49,555 --> 00:07:53,751
I waited in the sun for 15 minutes. Do
you know how many freckles I have now?

123
00:07:53,823 --> 00:07:56,249
- I'm sorry.
- Calm down, Yuko.

124
00:07:56,255 --> 00:07:58,318
You take your freckles way too seriously.

125
00:07:58,453 --> 00:08:01,217
No, I don't! It's a major problem for me.

126
00:08:01,223 --> 00:08:03,745
Aren't either of you
concerned about your exams?

127
00:08:03,822 --> 00:08:05,779
Now get out and go study.

128
00:08:06,813 --> 00:08:08,438
I got it!

129
00:08:09,132 --> 00:08:11,670
Here! This way.

130
00:08:12,219 --> 00:08:14,010
Kick it harder than that.

131
00:08:14,339 --> 00:08:16,848
I wrote some lyrics for
our graduation ceremony,

132
